 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-vkc","title":"CLI: SpeedScore Display and Management Commands","description":"## Overview
Add CLI commands for viewing and managing SpeedScores, including display in worker lists and manual benchmark triggering.

## Background and Justification
Users need visibility into SpeedScores from the command line without opening the web dashboard. This is essential for:
- Quick debugging of worker selection decisions
- Triggering benchmarks on new workers
- Viewing score history
- Understanding why a particular worker was chosen

## New Commands

### 1. rch workers list --speedscore
Enhance existing workers list to show SpeedScore:

```
$ rch workers list --speedscore

ID       STATUS      SLOTS   SPEEDSCORE  TREND   LAST BENCHMARKED
css      healthy     8/48    85 ████████  ↑ +3   2 hours ago
csd      healthy     4/48    83 ████████  → 0    2 hours ago
fmd      healthy     0/16    72 ███████   ↓ -5   1 day ago
yto      unreachable 0/8     68 ██████    -      3 days ago
new      healthy     0/8     N/A         -      never

Workers sorted by SpeedScore (descending)
Average SpeedScore: 77.0
```

